---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Separator from "../components/Separator.astro";
import StorefrontSection from "../components/StorefrontSection.astro";

const title = "Hello | PCLIKA";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description="A public letter to makers, developers, and AI hardware builders exploring Pclika.">
  <section class="hello-page">
    <StorefrontSection
      eyebrow="Open Letter"
      title="Build, Play & Monetize Your Hardware with Pclika"
      description="A simple introduction to what Pclika stands for, who it is for, and how creators can turn ideas into real hardware products."
    />
    <Separator />

    <article class="hello-letter">
      <p>Hey Makers, Developers, and AI Hardware Enthusiasts,</p>

      <p>
        If you are an Embedded Developer, Edge AI Developer, Hardware Developer, Firmware Developer, Model Deployment Developer,
        Agent Developer, Skill Developer, Full-stack Developer, or AI/ML Engineer, this is your open playground.
        Pclika is an open hardware ecosystem built for easy creation, fun innovation, and real commercial output, with no high threshold and no complex restrictions.
      </p>

      <p>
        Our core rule is simple: anyone can easily build exclusive Pclika hardware. We have already sorted out the underlying hardware architecture,
        base frameworks, and technical foundations. You do not need to start from scratch. You can focus on creativity and ideas, and turn them into unique hardware products faster.
      </p>

      <p>
        Best of all, your creations belong entirely to you. Once your hardware project is ready, you can sell it directly or launch it through crowdfunding.
        You keep product ownership and profit returns, so your technical exploration can become real commercial value.
      </p>

      <div class="hello-block">
        <p class="hello-block__title">One-stop hardware support</p>
        <p>
          To let every developer innovate with less burden and focus on scenario creation, Pclika provides a full-process hardware support system:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>PCB design, board making, and prototype verification</li>
          <li>SMT patch processing and component assembly production</li>
          <li>Professional hardware debugging and performance optimization</li>
          <li>Small-batch trial production and mass-production docking support</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="hello-block">
        <p class="hello-block__title">Rich and playable application scenarios</p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            Embedded and MCU smart hardware scenarios for portable sensing modules, controllers, wearables, and interactive intelligent devices.
          </li>
          <li>
            Edge AI local intelligent scenarios for offline voice interaction, local image recognition, environmental intelligence, and low-latency AI computing.
          </li>
          <li>
            AI Agent smart body hardware scenarios for autonomous desktop robots, smart IoT terminals, and hardware that can think, plan, and act independently.
          </li>
          <li>
            Custom Skill interactive hardware scenarios for scheduling, data monitoring, device linkage, and personalized scene behavior.
          </li>
          <li>
            Innovative consumer and industrial small hardware, from playful gadgets and desktop devices to compact intelligent industrial terminals.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <p>
        Pclika makes hardware development easy, fun, and valuable. Turn your technical ideas into playable, sellable, and innovative hardware products with a much lower entry barrier.
      </p>

      <p class="hello-signoff">Pclika Team</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hello-page {
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .hello-letter {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 58rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 0 0;
  }

  .hello-letter p,
  .hello-letter li {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-alt);
  }

  .hello-block {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    padding: 1rem 0;
  }

  .hello-block__title {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .hello-letter ul,
  .hello-letter ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.7rem;
  }

  .hello-signoff {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
